 Malebranche’s theory of grace, retracing his claims regarding the nature of creation and the relation between God and world and between God and Jesus. Through Malebranche, Badiou develops a radical concept of truth and the subject. This book renders a seemingly obscure post-Cartesian philosopher fascinating and alive, restoring him to the philosophy canon. It occupies a pivotal place in Badiou’s reflections on the nature of being that demonstrates the crucial role of theology in his thinking.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 7aPHILOSOPHY / Individual Philosophers.2bisacsh1 aBadiou, Alain, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReinhard, Kenneth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReinhard, Kenneth, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSmith, Jason E.1 aSmith, Jason E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSpitzer, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSpitzer, Susan.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065195908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2019 Englishz978311061055008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2019z9783110606423oZDB-23-DPH40uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/badi1747840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231548533423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780231548533/original  a978-3-11-061055-0  EBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 201